body:
KeyedLoadIC entrypoints and generic paths are emitted by AccessorAssembler in ic/accessor-assembler.cc. Notable public generators:
- void AccessorAssembler::GenerateKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic() at lines ~4692-4706: tail-calls KeyedLoadICGeneric.
- void AccessorAssembler::GenerateKeyedLoadICTrampoline_Megamorphic() at ~4744-4754: trampoline to Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic.
- void AccessorAssembler::GenerateKeyedLoadIC_PolymorphicName() at ~4757-4771: enters KeyedLoadICPolymorphicName.
The shared slow/generic helpers:
- void AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadICGeneric(const LoadICParameters* p) at ~3728-3804: does elements-vs-properties dispatch, calls GenericElementLoad or GenericPropertyLoad and uses Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic.
- void AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadICPolymorphicName(const LoadICParameters* p, LoadAccessMode) at ~3811-3838: probes feedback array for polymorphic name IC, then HandlePolymorphicCase.
Dispatch from feedback:
- At ~3604-3720, AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadIC (inlined control) handles monomorphic via TryMonomorphicCase, polymorphic via HandlePolymorphicCase when feedback is WeakFixedArray, and megamorphic fallback to Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic; also has PolymorphicName subcase when key is unique name.
explanation: Captures the JS entry stub/builtin entrypoints and generic KeyedLoadIC dispatch implemented in AccessorAssembler, which are the first stage from JS into the IC machinery for a[i] loads.
